  "prompt": "What will be my rank if I have scored 132/200 in MU-OET?",
  "response": "Determining your rank based on a specific score in the Manipal University Online Entrance Test (MU-OET) is challenging without specific data for a given year, as rankings depend on the relative performance of all the test-takers. The rank is influenced by:\n\n1. **Overall Performance of Candidates**: Your rank depends on how other candidates perform. If many score higher than 132, your rank will be lower than if fewer score higher.\n\n2. **Difficulty Level of the Exam**: If the test is particularly hard in a given year, a score of 132 might result in a higher percentile and thus a better rank.\n\n3. **Total Number of Candidates**: The more candidates there are, the more competition you face for a higher rank.\n\nEach year's results can vary, so it\u2019s best to refer to historical data from previous years or official notifications from Manipal University regarding that specific year's results. Additionally, consider checking with students' forums or university guidance services for more up-to-date estimates.",
